<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.171364>
    dc:description "FIGURE 8. A, Apopontonia disparostris Bruce, NORFANZ stn. 20. B, Hamiger novaezealandiae Borradaile, NORFANZ stn. 133, male. C, Periclimenes fenneri sp. nov., holotype, NOR­ FANZ stn. 154. D, Periclimenes tangeroa sp. nov., holotype, NORFANZ stn. 0 0 6. Scale bars in millemeters." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/171364/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.171362>
    dc:description "FIGURE 5. Periclimenes tangeroa sp. nov., ovigerous female holotype. A, carapace and antennae, dorsal. B, anterior carapace and left antennae, dorsal. C, rostrum. D, antennular peduncle. E, antenna. F, posterior abdominal segments, lateral. G, telson. H, same, posterior spines. I, uropod." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/171362/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.171363>
    dc:description "FIGURE 7. Periclimenes tangeroa sp. nov., ovigerous female holotype. A, third pereiopod dactyl, distal corpus and unguis. Third pereiopod dactyls, not to scale, adjusted to same basal depth. B, Periclimenes tangeroa sp. nov. C, Periclimenes alcocki Kemp (redrawn from Bruce, 1996). A, scale bar 0.2 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/171363/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

